<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Henry, Alexander. Travels in the Red River Department (Abridged), 1806. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0024</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">76</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw">1806</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">part of the North West.  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>fter collecting Buffaloe Dung we made a fire of it by which we cooked<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Afresh breeze drove away the Musq<span class="AddHand-editors">[ui]</span>toes, placed a guard and went to bed &#8212; pleased for being so far advanced upon our Journey <span class="AddHand-author">towards</span> home.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednesday 30</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Up early, proceeded in the same course as yesterday &#8212; a great quantity of water in the plains which some times reached the horses bellies and made our progress slow.  Encamped at a small lake.  I as<span class="DelHand-author">s</span>ended a high hill From which I had a pleasant view<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thursday 31<sup>st</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">It rained hard during the night which still continuing this morning accompanied with a thick fog &#8212; and an illness that seized me, detained us all this day in the same place<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday Aug<sup>t</sup> 1<sup>st</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Still bad weather and I still unwell we however proceeded and in the afternoon came to the ridge of land which seperates the waters of the Missisouri and Asseneboine<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  From this Eminence we could see Thousands of Buffaloes in all directions over a Beautiful country<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  A Storm obliged us to encamp at an early hour<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Saturday 2<sup>nd</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The storm still continuing prevented our departure.  Some of our men went to hunt and killed a few Buffaloes.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sunday 3<sup>rd</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The weather having cleared up we of course</p>
<p style="text-align:right;"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">moved</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[80]</span></p>

